Description: Basic constituent of lecithin that is found in many plants and animal organs. It is an essential nutrient for human.

Name: 3,4-Dihydroxybenzaldehyde
Description: 3,4-Dihydroxybenzaldehyde, also known as protocatechuic aldehyde, is a phenolic aldehyde, a compound released from cork stoppers into wine.

Name: D-Galactose
Description: D-Galactose is an aldohexose that occurs naturally in the D-form in lactose, cerebrosides, gangliosides, and mucoproteins.

Name: 3-Caffeoylquinic acid
Synonyms: Neochlorogenic acid; 5-Caffeoylquinic acid [Old IUPAC, before 1976]; KEGG:C17147
Description: There is a confusion between two IUPAC nomenclatures. 5-CQA and 3-CQA should respectively correspond to chlorogenic acid and neochlorogenic acid. However many databases and publications still use the former nomenclature.

Name: 4-Methoxyphenylacetic acid sulfate
Synonyms: p-Methoxyphenylacetic acid sulfate; p-Methoxy-alpha-toluic acid sulfate; Homoanisic acid sulfate
Description: Degradation product of 2-phenylacetic acid (pmid:23831706).

Name: 2-Oxoarginine
Synonyms: 2-oxo-5-Guanidinopentanoic acid; 5-Guanidino-2-oxovaleric acid; alpha-Keto-delta-guanidinovaleric acid; 5-Carbamimidamido-2-oxopentanoic acid; 5-Guanidino-2-oxopentanoic acid

Name: Metanephrine
Description: Metanephrine is a metabolite of epinephrine.

Name: Aspartylhistidine
Description: Dipeptide composed of aspartate and histidine.

Name: 2-Oxobutyric acid
Synonyms: 2-Oxobutanoic acid; 2-Ketobutyric acid; 2-Ketobutanoic acid; alpha-Ketobutyric acid; 3-Methylpyruvic acid

Name: N-Acetylglycine
Synonyms: Acetylglycine; Acetamidoacetic acid; Aceturic acid; Ethanoylaminoethanoic acid

Name: 5-Methoxydimethyltryptamine
Description: A psychedelic of the tryptamine class.

Name: Uric acid
Description: A product of the metabolic breakdown of purine nucleotides, and a normal component of urine.

Name: Orotic acid
Description: An intermediate product in pyrimidine synthesis which plays a role in chemical conversions between dihydrofolate and tetrahydrofolate.

Name: Agmatine
Description: Decarboxylation product of arginine. Isolated from several plant and animal sources. Precursor for polyamine synthesis.

Name: Oxaloacetic acid
Description: Intermediate in the Krebs cycle.

Name: Nt-Methylhistamine
Description: Metabolite of histamine (pmid:6524522).

Name: Alanine betaine
Synonyms: beta-Alanine betaine; N-Trimethylalanine; Trimethylalanine; Propiobetaine; beta-Homobetaine; 3-N-Trimethylaminopropionic acid

Name: 5-Aminovaleric acid betaine
Synonyms: delta-Aminovaleric acid betaine; delta-Valerobetaine; 5-AVAB; N,N,N-Trimethyl-5-aminovaleric acid; TMAVA; 5-Aminopentanoic acid betaine
Description: This betainized compound has been detected in human plasma and positively associated with the intake of carbohydrates (pmid:31504116).

Name: Urolithin A
Description: Metabolite of ellagic acid

Name: Coumaric acids
Description: This includes o-, m- and p-coumaric acid. p-Coumaric acid is the most abundant isomer of the three in nature.

Name: Hydroxybenzoic acids
Description: This includes 2-, 3- and 4-hydroxybenzoic acid.

Name: 5,10-Ethenyl-tetrahydrofolyl-polyglutamic acid
Description: Chemical structure is represented with a tail of 3 glutamic acids.

Name: Glycerol 3-phosphate
Description: Glycerol 3-phosphate is a chemical intermediate in the glycolysis metabolic pathway (hmdb).

Name: 3alpha,12alpha-Dihydroxy-5alpha-cholenoic acid
Description: Undefined structure. According to publication where described, it could be "3alpha,12alpha-Dihydroxy-5alpha-chol-6-enoic acid" or "3alpha,12alpha-Dihydroxy-5alpha-chol-8,14-enoic acid".

Name: Stercobilinogen
Description: Bilirubin metabolite. Formed from I-Urobilinogen. Precursor of stercobilin.
